Program: The History Hour
Title: Remembering Chernobyl
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03rxtd5
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 2 May 2016
Chernobyl, the world's worst nuclear disaster; the funeral of Charles Darwin, whose theory of evolution changed the world; plus, the impact of being accused during the McCarthy era in America, and two style icons of the Sixties, the Mini and Yves St Laurent. Photo: a Swedish farmer wears protective clothing because of contamination from the Chernobyl nuclear disaster (Credit: STF/AFP/Getty Images) Show less